<TITLE> 4 Tahrir men on 2 day remand </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 9 (bdnews24.com)---A Dhaka court on Sunday granted police two days to interrogate four members of banned Islamist outfit Hizb-ut-Tahrir's Dhaka University unit . The arrested students are Rafiqul Islam Parash, 2nd year student of finance, Nayan and Abdul Hye Raju, 3rd year students of the same department and Mohsin Hossain, 3rd year student of the accounting. The judge, Ismail Hossain, of Dhaka Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court on Sunday granted the police two days to quiz the detainees after Shahbagh police sub-inspector Abdul Malek asked for seven days. After the hearing, the magistrate granted two days, general recording officer SI Ratan Sheikh told bdnews24.com. Investigation officer of the case said they were members of the banned Islamist outfit Hizb-ut-Tahrir and involved with the outfits operations. It is crucial to grill them to track down their associates, he said. A case was filed with Shahbagh police on Sunday against the detained learners under 2009 anti-terrorism law. The Shahbagh police arrested the four activists of Chhatra Mukti from Surja Sen hall at around 2am on charges of distributing leaflets on the campus the day before, university proctor KM Saiful Islam said. A lot of Jihadist literature was also recovered from their rooms, the proctor said. Islam explained that the police came to arrest the four students as one of them, Raju, had handed a leaflet to a student of the hall, and other students had informed the authorities about this. Police then came to the hall and arrested Raju. The three other students were arrested on the basis of Raju's statement, the proctor said. Islam said they apprehended that there might be activists in other halls of the university too. "We will speak to the teachers and decide our next course of action," he said. Police last month arrested the main coordinator of the Islamist outfit Mahiuddin Ahmed, an associate professor of the Institute of Business Administration of Dhaka University. DU authoritie